3. [MEDIUM] Architectural Gaps & Stability
A. The "Buffer" Crash (Vite + Solana)
Solana’s web3.js library relies on Node.js Buffer. Vite does not provide this by default. The
app will likely crash the moment a user attempts to sign a message or interact with the
blockchain.
●
Remedy: Install vite-plugin-node-polyfills and enable it in vite.config.js.
B. Direct window.solana Usage (Brittle Logic)
Manually calling window.solana is insecure and does not support mobile deep-linking or
standardized error handling.
●
Remedy: Refactor to use the official @solana/wallet-adapter-react and
@solana/wallet-adapter-phantom libraries.
C. Manual Fetch Wrapper vs. Axios
The current request function in api.js is prone to race conditions during token refresh
(multiple 401s firing at once).
●
Remedy: Migrate to Axios. Use Interceptors to automatically attach JWTs and handle
the Nonce-based signature headers for Web3 requests.
